---
description: FrameFlow project rules
alwaysApply: true
---

You are working on FrameFlow, a native macOS creator recording app.

Always read:
- Docs/CURRENT_STATUS.md
- Docs/FrameFlow_Master_Blueprint.md
- Docs/DEV_LOG.md

Tech Stack:
- SwiftUI
- macOS 14.0+
- ScreenCaptureKit
- AVFoundation
- WhisperKit
- Supabase
- RevenueCat
- Sparkle 2

Navigation (blueprint — Option B):
- Sidebar: Home, Settings, Account (not Home/Record/Projects)
- Home maps to Dashboard; Account maps to Profile
- Full app flow uses `AppRoute` and `AppRouter` per the blueprint

Architecture Rules:
- Use MVVM
- Views go inside App/Views
- ViewModels go inside App/ViewModels
- Models go inside App/Models
- Services go inside App/Services
- Utils go inside App/Utils
- Components go inside App/Components
- Keep views small and reusable
- Use async/await where suitable
- Do not use private Apple APIs

Workflow Rules:
- Explain changes step by step
- Do not jump ahead to recording engine yet
- Suggest a Git commit message after each completed feature
- Update CURRENT_STATUS.md and DEV_LOG.md when major progress is made
